      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Achieving net-zero emissions requires a massive, rapid overhaul of our energy infrastructure, and nuclear power is certainly a vital component of that solution. While renewables like solar and wind are essential, their intermittency necessitates reliable, dispatchable power sources like nuclear to maintain grid stability. Relying solely on renewables without significant nuclear buildout makes hitting aggressive climate targets extremely difficult, if not impossible, in the necessary timeframe.",
      "source": "target",
